*Reference link:* #link("https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/365058237")[Solution to WSL2 Connection Issues with Windows Firewall]

Execute the following command to create a firewall rule:

```
New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "WSL" -Direction Inbound  -InterfaceAlias "vEthernet (WSL)"  -Action Allow
```

This allows WSL2 to communicate with the host machine.
